Here's a summary of the changes I made to fix the bug:

## Changes Made

**File: `src/main/java/io/github/hectorvent/floci/services/eventbridge/EventBridgeService.java`**

### 1. Forward the `Resources` array in `buildEventEnvelope` (line 475-486)

Previously, the `resources` field in the event envelope was always set to an empty array (`node.putArray("resources")`). Now it forwards the `Resources` list from the event entry if present:

```java
Object resourcesObj = entry.get("Resources");
if (resourcesObj instanceof List<?> resourcesList) {
    var resourcesArray = node.putArray("resources");
    for (Object resource : resourcesList) {
        if (resource != null) {
            resourcesArray.add(resource.toString());
        }
    }
} else {
    node.putArray("resources");
}
```

### 2. Add `resources` pattern matching in `matchesPattern` (lines 373-379)

Added handling for the `resources` field in the event pattern, so rules can filter events by resource ARNs:

```java
JsonNode resourcesField = pattern.get("resources");
if (resourcesField != null && resourcesField.isArray()) {
    Object eventResources = event.get("Resources");
    if (!matchesResourcesField(resourcesField, eventResources)) {
        return false;
    }
}
```

### 3. New `matchesResourcesField` helper method (lines 416-433)

Added a helper method that checks if any of the event's resources match any of the pattern's resources, similar to how `matchesArrayField` works for single values:

```java
private boolean matchesResourcesField(JsonNode arrayNode, Object resources) {
    if (resources == null) return false;
    List<?> resourceList;
    if (resources instanceof List<?> list) {
        resourceList = list;
    } else {
        return false;
    }
    for (Object resource : resourceList) {
        String resourceStr = resource != null ? resource.toString() : null;
        for (JsonNode element : arrayNode) {
            if (resourceStr != null && resourceStr.equals(element.asText())) {
                return true;
            }
        }
    }
    return false;
}
```

